==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chatter mark
<hw>Chat"ter mark`</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Mach.)</fld> <def>One of the
fine undulations or ripples which are formed on the surface of work by a
cutting tool which chatters.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>A short crack on a rock surface planed smooth by a
glacier.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chattiness</ent>⟦br⟧
